<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6397> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6397" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Praefectus Classis in Octavian's fleet (SEG 4.102; NS 1924, 511ff.), the officer whom Menodorus approached when preparing to redesert to Octavian (App. BC 5.102). Besides Oppius Capito and Statilius Taurus (see above, Promagistrates), Grant (From Imperium to Auctoritas 52-54) finds the names of other officers in the following inscriptions on coins issued in 37 and 36 at the naval base at Lipara: Sex. Ann., P. Corneli., L. Anni., An., L. Cae(cina?), Trebo[ni.], D. Por.(?), Sacer.., P. Al., P. Calp., M. Aufi. Scaeva. Their position and identity remain uncertain." .
